				<wikidot:authorName>RedFive99</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3433962</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I agree. The Foundation wouldn't allow anything like that, as the anomaly and its method of spreading aren't fully understood. Eating I could possibly understand as an experiment, but it would cause the unnecessary destruction of an SCP, which would prevent any further experimentation. As for the dog, though it's a cute concept — and admittedly made me smile — it just seems like careless containment and a lack of objectivity. Plus, some people are allergic to dogs. Aside from that, the story was enjoyable and oddly unnerving.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
