					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The central concept is intriguing enough and well-presented enough that this deserves an upvote, though the depiction of Soft Hands (TM) is a serious weak point for this article. I like the idea of a anomaly deciding to 'increase production' because they think the Foundation appreciates it, and this conceit makes the 'notes to the Foundation' device much more palatable than it normally is. Unfortunately the presentation of Soft Hands as purveyors of Creepy Broken English (TM) without much else to convey is pretty bland and well-trodden enough that it takes away from the article.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
